trend_summary: Across the series the landscape remains overwhelmingly agricultural with scattered farmsteads. The chief change is the creation of a mid‐reach reservoir, accompanied by modest field reconfiguration and small forest clearances. Housing grows only marginally along the main road, leaving built-up density sparse and the character firmly rural.
notable_changes: New reservoir/lake excavated and filled in the central–eastern sector between the second and third images.
Clearance of several wooded plots for pasture or crops, especially south-central and southeast.
Incremental addition of isolated houses/farm buildings along the north-edge arterial road.
Crop rotation patterns alter field colours annually, with some plots reverting from brown fallow to green cover.
Minor reforestation or natural regrowth on a few former fields west of the reservoir.
